## When to deviate from reference-impl

The reference impl is a working substrate, not a prescription. Use
`alternatives.md` to pick a different runtime if any of these apply:

- The team needs a hosted runtime (no VPS / cron access) → n8n.cloud
  or Pipedream
- The team needs durable workflows with retry semantics → Temporal
  or Inngest
- The team's deployer prefers Python → custom Python runner
- The team is enterprise + needs RBAC → custom Python or n8n self-hosted
  with auth
- The team's audit + compliance posture needs centralized logging
  (CloudWatch, Datadog, etc.) → adapt the audit-log emission

The CONTRACTS (kill switch, approval, audit shape) stay constant
regardless of runtime.

## Verification checklist

The team is "built" when ALL of these pass:

- [ ] Every agent wakes on its trigger, exits cleanly
- [ ] Every L3+ tool call from a `semi`/`supervised` agent triggers
      Telegram approval
- [ ] `/approve` unblocks; `/deny` blocks
- [ ] Approval timeout escalates per tier ladder
- [ ] Kill switch (file flag, env var, `/halt-all`) all halt the team
      within one cron tick
- [ ] Audit logs are append-only, redacted, schema-conformant
- [ ] PII redaction passes the test fixtures in `governance/pii-redaction.md`
- [ ] Each workflow's success criteria (per `workflows/<id>.md`) is
      met by an end-to-end run

